		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>Wondrous Item - Very Rare</em></p><p><em>A magic item like this counts as magical for overcoming effects. This mirror is 4 ft. tall, 2 ft. wide, 50 lb.</em></p><p>AC 11, HP 10, Immunity to Poison and Psychic, Vulnerability to Bludgeoning. Destroyed at 0 HP.</p><p><strong>Trap Creature</strong></p><p><strong>Action</strong> - 1 Creature (30 ft.)</p><p>While hanging and within 5 feet, speak the command word to activate; repeat to deactivate. When activated</p><p><strong>[[/save CHA 15]]{Charisma Save (DC 15)}</strong></p><p>Creatures aware of the mirror have Advantage; &amp;reference[Construct] succeed automatically.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure: </strong>Target is trapped (along with its gear) in one of 12 extradimensional cells. Cells are fog-filled, infinite, and suspend aging, eating, drinking, and sleeping. A creature can escape only via planar travel; otherwise remains until freed. If all 12 cells are full, a random trapped creature is freed to hold a new prisoner. If the mirror is shattered, all creatures inside are freed nearby.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> No effect.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Interact with Mirror</strong></p><p><em>Trigger: While within 5 ft. of the Mirror</em></p><ul><li><p>Name a trapped creature or call a cell number; that creature appears as an image on the surface and can communicate. Take a Action and use a second command word to free one trapped creature; it and its possessions appear in the nearest unoccupied space facing away from the mirror.</p></li></ul><p><em>Placing the mirror inside an extradimensional space (@UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-magic-items.Item.Ml4IiFoTZRXt7rw7]{Bag of Holding}, @UUID[Compendium.elkan5e.elkan5e-magic-items.Item.dmgPortableHole0]{Portable Hole}, etc.) destroys both and opens a one-way gate to the Astral Plane, pulling creatures within 10 feet not behind Total Cover to a random Astral location.</em></p><section class=\"secret\" id=\"foundry-secret-1\"><p><strong>Foundry Note</strong></p><p>This item has a max uses of 12 which can be used to track the number of creatures trapped within the mirror. The <strong>Add/Free Trapped Creature</strong> activities can be used to increment/decrement that number.</p></section>",
